history.content:
EE127. No reason to take Math 110 if you do 127 + math 54. EE126 is for math maturity + probabilistic perspective but you're taking 189 with Shewchuck and planning to use ML just for industry so even though 126 is the recommended choice, realistically speaking it's probably more difficult and intensive than you need.

You should probably watch out for the release of DS102 next semester, which is applied Machine Learning and a new course. I would recommend this over 189.

EE127. No reason to take Math 110 if you do 127 + math 54. EE126 is for math maturity + probabilistic perspective but you're taking 189 with Shewchuck and planning to use ML just for industry so even though 126 is the recommended choice, realistically speaking it's probably more difficult and intensive than you need.

My goal is to have a good enough understanding of 189 to be able to work on ML related things in industry.

Courses related to or "prep" for 189 I've taken are DS100, CS188, Math 54, CS70, & EE16a.

I plan on taking 189 in the Spring. If I only have room to take one of the following courses to prepare for 189 which would you recommend?

Math110, EECS126, or EECS127
